Company Description
Seja em áreas de mobilidade, bens de consumo, tecnologia industrial, energia e de construção ou no desenvolvimento de novos modelos de negócios: A Bosch faz uma contribuição decisiva para melhorar a qualidade de vida desta geração e das que virão. Isto só é possível com um network global de mais de 410 mil colaboradores altamente comprometidos, que quebram barreiras todos os dias.

Job Description
Our Bosch Team is responsible for building the connected vehicle platform, supporting and creating new data driven services for Bosch customers. Our company is looking for a SW Developer that will actuate in back-end development and support for connectivity platforms.

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Electronics / Software / Computer engineer/science or related fields;
Good ability to communicate in English, in technical and business settings (verbal and written);
Experience in backend development and data engineering;
Basic skills for usage of different data warehouse and ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) and streaming architectures, distributed computing (e.g. in Hadoop).
Deep understanding of system design, data structures and algorithms;
Experienced with modern backend languages, technologies, coding, testing, debugging, and automation;
Maintain system architecture documentation;
Experience in AIoT, connectivity and mobility are considered a differentiation;
You enjoy learning quickly and working closely together with your product team to bring value to your partners;
Picks up new technology quickly;
Strong attention to details;
Curiosity;
Maker spirit.
Additional Information
Prazo de candidatura: 23/05/2022 às 17h00
Área: PS/BDO-LA
Colaboradores Bosch: recomendamos comunicar seu gestor após candidatura.
Benefícios
Além de te proporcionar uma incrível experiência e desenvolvimento profissional, também contamos com o nosso pacote de benefícios:
Aqui você tem garantida uma assistência médica e odontológica de qualidade para você, além de iniciativas de saúde que visam te apoiar no cuidado com sua qualidade de vida;
Temos também convênios com farmácias e/ou políticas de subsídio para compra de medicamentos;
Nossas plantas contam com restaurantes próprios com alimentação de qualidade (nas localidades em que não temos essa estrutura, oferecemos VA);
Contamos com fretado para facilitar seu deslocamento e/ou auxílio transporte, bem como vagas em estacionamento interno sem custo, caso prefira vir com carro próprio;
Ofertamos benefícios de fim de ano para você e sua família;
Seguro de vida;
Auxílio material escolar no início do ano;
Clube para atividades esportivas e de lazer.
Vaga elegível para pessoa com deficiência ou reabilitada.

Company Description
SGS is the world’s leading inspection, verification, testing and certification company. SGS is recognized as the global benchmark for quality and integrity. With more than 93,000 employees, SGS operates a network of over 2,400 offices and laboratories around the world.
We provide the world’s most comprehensive range of integrated inspection, testing, certification and advisory services, powered by the latest technology and digital tools. Our solutions enable our clients to identify and validate new innovations, products, services and business models to build consumer trust and operate more efficiently and securely.

Job Description
Working as part of an Artificial Intelligence squad, you will partner with a Scrum Master and Engineers to develop and release new AI solutions and use cases for our five business units at speed and scale. You will design the analytics framework that will go into the solution.
More specifically, you will:
Participate in all aspects of agile software development including design, development, implementation, test and deployment;
Architect, model, and assist in the development of services to support internal and external business needs;
Use a combined knowledge of computer science and applications, modelling, statistics, analytics and maths to solve problems;
Work across the full data stack, building highly scalable models that enable unique and useful insight into the data;
Perform data discovery, preparation, model planning, model building, operation, presentation and visualisation;
Planning for a model by using different statistical formulas and visualization tools;
Distribute datasets for training and testing; Techniques like association, classification, and clustering can be applied to the training data sets;
Actively contribute to the squad rituals such as planning meetings, standups, and retrospects.

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field (Machine Learning, Mathematics, Computer Science, Statistics, Physics, Engineering, etc);
Must have experience using at least one of the following, R, SAS, Python, SQL, Hive, Matlab, Pig, Spark, Jupyter notebooks and git;
Knowledge of various DBMS technology such as MySQL, MongoDB, Oracle, SQLServer;
Experience exploring, analyzing and visualizing datasets using visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, Qlik;
Experience or interest in Natural Language Processing (NLP);
Fluent in English.
Additional Information
This position will be based at our Emerging Tech Centre in Graz.
